name: 9. Roasted vegetables.
description:
"This garden has endured cows, fowls, chickens, minor periods of neglect, drought and frosts. We cried when the first fence failed and the neighbors Cattle turned up, not to eat anything but just stomp and crap all over it. We laughed and danced when the first successful crops were raised; fresh roquette with every meal, tomatoes preserving on the shelf and so much thyme. But we didn't feel much at all when it was finally roasted. Only the inevitability of defeat, inherent in attempting to "grow your own food" danced and laughed in our minds."

Photography by Jay Moon, during the Australian wildfires; November 2019.
#9 of 15.
All funds generated go toward the ongoing recovery.
